OL,3,CUnpaid carers tell of exhaustion and
OL,4,Cfrustration with a system in crisis
OL,6,FOver the years Susan Osborne has
OL,7,Fprovided full time care to five
OL,8,Fdifferent family members and she has
OL,9,Fnever earned a penny doing it.
OL,11,FShe still looks after her disabled
OL,12,Fdaughter, brother in law, and husband
OL,13,FJohn at their home in Wythenshawe,
OL,14,FManchester.
OL,16,FSusan says it's exhausting. "With John
OL,17,Fat the moment, it's everything,
OL,18,Fbecause he can't move so I'm cooking
OL,19,Fcleaning, he can hardly move out of
OL,20,Fthe chair I'm having to help him with
OL,21,Fhis walking and in the bath.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/10
