OL,3,CUnpaid carers tell of exhaustion and
OL,4,Cfrustration with a system in crisis
OL,6,F"It's a nightmare at the moment, it's
OL,7,Fvery stressful and sometimes I'm so
OL,8,Ftired, you know, and then I get
OL,9,Firritable and then I get snappy and I
OL,10,Fdon't mean to but it's really, really
OL,11,Fhard for carers."
OL,13,FAnd what makes it even harder is the
OL,14,Fmoney worries.
OL,16,FSusan had to give up her job to care
OL,17,Ffor her family and the carer's
OL,18,Fallowance she gets comes with caveats.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/10
