OL,3,CUnpaid carers tell of exhaustion and
OL,4,Cfrustration with a system in crisis
OL,6,F"83 pound a week. It's not a lot of
OL,7,Fmoney. Now, it's taxable. So it's not
OL,8,Fa benefit, so the problem with that is
OL,9,Fthat because John's on benefits, they
OL,10,Ftake that off his benefits, they take
OL,11,Fhalf of it.
OL,13,FSo although they give me the 83, they
OL,14,Ftake 40 pound off him. The politicians
OL,15,Fdon't understand how we survive,
OL,16,Freally, because they don't have to."
OL,18,FEvery carer's story is unique but
OL,19,Fthere are many more stories to tell.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
