OL,3,CUnpaid carers tell of exhaustion and
OL,4,Cfrustration with a system in crisis
OL,6,F"We also see the impact on local
OL,7,Fauthorities and local councils, so for
OL,8,Fmany local councils, the majority of
OL,9,Ftheir budget goes to paying for social
OL,10,Fcare, adults social care and
OL,11,Fchildren's social care, and that means
OL,12,Fless money for bus services, for
OL,13,Flibraries, and a declining trust in
OL,14,Four local government.
OL,16,F"We are already seeing the impacts,
OL,17,Fand so the solutions are really
OL,18,Furgent. We need to find a way to pay
OL,19,Ffor care, which is affordable both to
OL,20,Findividuals and to the taxpayer.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/10
